03/06/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu met on Thursday (2 June) with directors of the main independent media in the country to discuss the upcoming election campaign and the media's role in the process.
Moisiu expressed hope that local media would help the 3 July elections be held according to international standards.
He asked for coverage that is impartial and professional.
Also Thursday, the OSCE Presence in Albania released a report to the OSCE Permanent Council acknowledging major progress in the style of election campaigns.
The report concludes that in contrast to previous elections, the parties and candidates are outlining platforms and policy proposals that attempt to answer quality-of-life concerns of the public.
(Albanian news, Albanian President Web site - 03/06/05)
